HEADWORD: Thermotaxis
<hw>Ther`mo*tax"is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.;
<ets>thermo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ an arranging.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The property possessed by protoplasm of moving under
the influence of heat.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Determination of the
direction of locomotion by heat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermotensile</ent>⟦br⟧
